race.comment: Prepared to give GIRL'S GOT CLASS (5) another chance. Was on speed and boxed on fairly in a richer maiden last time but will appreciate this level and is expected to take catching. RENEGE (3) is fitter for two runs in and looks close to getting off the mark. Fought on well last time and with the blinkers added gets his chance. SPLASH OF WHITE (8) was tested over further last time in and ran some decent races in richer maidens. Fitter for a trial and drawn for a soft run stalking the lead. SHIMAZY (6) is much better than last start and will find this more to her liking. Very lightly raced for a seven-year-old mare and will be winding up late off the low draw. UNCOMMON MIND (10) was heavily bet on debut and finished midfield, beaten a few lengths. Well weighed again and drawn to improve.
